%I A394564 #5 Mar 24 2026 20:47:17
%S A394564 1,2,6,8,21
%N A394564 Least integer a(n) such that every graph on n vertices has an induced subgraph of order n.
%C A394564 a(6)>=28 and a(7)>=48. It is not known if the sequence is increasing.
%H A394564 S. Fajtlowicz, T. McColgan, T. Read, and W. Staton, <a href="https://combinatorialpress.com/article/ars/Volume%20039/volume-39-paper-15.pdf">Ramsey numbers for induced regular subgraphs</a>, Ars Combinatoria, 39 (1995) 149-154.
%e A394564 a(3)=6 because some graphs with 5 vertices (for example the 5-cycle) have no induced regular subgraph of order 3, but every graph with 6 vertices has one.
%Y A394564 Cf. A394563
%K A394564 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A394564 1,2
%A A394564 _Brendan McKay_, Mar 24 2026
